# AskPDF Landing Page — Dark Glassmorphism UI

Build a premium dark-mode glassmorphism landing page for AskPDF using the `custom-vibe` skill, adapting the DeFi template recipe to the PDF-AI product context.

## Project Structure Findings

```
app/web/
├── app/
│   ├── globals.css        ← OVERWRITE (v4 Tailwind syntax, needs v3 skill format)
│   ├── layout.tsx         ← MODIFY (swap Geist → Inter, update metadata)
│   ├── page.tsx           ← OVERWRITE (assemble Navbar + Hero + BrandStrip)
│   └── api/...
├── postcss.config.mjs     ← KEEP (uses @tailwindcss/postcss — correct for v4)
├── next.config.ts         ← KEEP as-is
└── package.json           ← Tailwind v4 + @tailwindcss/postcss already installed
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tailwind v4 detected.** The project uses `tailwindcss@^4` + `@tailwindcss/postcss`. Tailwind v4 does **not** use a `tailwind.config.ts` file — tokens are defined directly in CSS using `@theme`. The skill's Section 2 (`tailwind.config.ts`) is v3 syntax and requires adaptation.
>
> The plan below translates all skill tokens to v4 `@theme {}` blocks inside `globals.css`.

> [!NOTE]
> shadcn/ui is **not** installed. The skill's Navbar and Hero use `<Button>` from `@/components/ui/button`. Rather than running the full shadcn init (which involves interactive prompts), we will create a minimal `Button` shim component inline, then install shadcn properly as a follow-up step.

